-- Brazil's economic activity rises 1.5 pct in July - central bank
-- 
-- Fri Sep 12, 2014 07:38AM EDT
-- None



BRASILIA, Sept 12 (Reuters) - The Brazilian central bank's IBC-Br economic activity index <BRIBC=ECI> rose 1.50 percent in July from June in seasonally adjusted terms, the bank said on Friday.

The median estimate in a Reuters survey of 21 analysts was for a 0.8 percent increase.